reviews.text: Delicious! The squid tentacles were absolutely succulent and tasty. All dishes I tried were very tasty, well presented and delicious. Prices are a tiny bit on the expensive side, but it was worth it. Service was polite and efficient, and seating comfortable. I would definitely come again.
Great meal. Quick service

Great food, and very filling with the addition of the $2 kaedama, or extra ramen. The dumplings were seared spot on, and the spicy variant (the dumplings themselves were the same; only the sauce was different) made it even more tempting than the original version. The limited clam ramen had a rich, clear broth and was generally better than the original ones, but it's probably just a matter of personal taste.
Service was pretty good at night.
